column1: Baby Barnaby's////My friend and I stumbled upon Baby Barnaby's after getting fed up with the waaaay too long brunch line at Snooze (we've all been there before). To be quite honest
column2: I wasn't too impressed with the variety on the menu at first. However
column4: and our wonderful server recommended it to us. Such a delicious and perfect plate! The flavors of the cheese
column6: and spinach in the eggs were perfect and melt in your mouth good. So satisfying when paired with crispy toast and potatoes after a long morning of waiting. Additionally
column7: their fresh squeezed grapefruit juice was wonderful. My only qualm was the size of that tiny cup for the price it was at. However
column8: our amazing server accidentally brought us an extra. Overall
column10: and I would definitely come again.
